cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD, cs.CL

The paper presents a novel approach based on the encoder-decoder deep learning framework with an attention mechanism for solving NILM. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks indicates that the paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also involves processing natural language, as it mentions the use of attention mechanisms in neural machine translation, text summarization, and speech recognition. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves processing time-series data, which suggests that it may also belong to the Signal and Data Processing (cs.SD) sub-category.
